    public interface Reversible
extends com.guidewire.bc.domain.accounting.gen.ReversibleStubI
    Applies to Transactions that can potentially be reversed.

    Objects that extend the Reversible interface can use the generic implentations found in ReversibleImpl. In this scenario, the extending object will generally keep a Reversible object, and the implementations for these methods will use the code in ReversibleImpl. For this to work, the extending object must implement the ReversibleImplCallback interface, which contains a few methods used in the generic ReversibleImpl code.
